# Rebrand-only template rule (DO NOT refactor layout)

This repo is a landing-page template. Maintain the existing **style**, **folder architecture**, and **mobile responsiveness**.

## Allowed changes (preferred)
- Update branding content in `src/constants/index.js` (copy, nav labels/anchors, products, links, emails, social alts).
- Swap assets in `src/assets/images/*` and `src/assets/icons/*` (logos, hero/product imagery).
- Adjust theme tokens in `tailwind.config.js` (brand colors only) while keeping utility class usage intact.
- Update document branding in `index.html` (title, favicon path).

## Forbidden changes (unless user explicitly requests)
- Do not reorganize folders or rename major directories (`src/components`, `src/sections`, `src/assets`, `src/constants`).
- Do not change section order in `src/App.jsx` or rewrite layout patterns (`padding*`, `max-container`, responsive breakpoints).
- Do not introduce new frameworks, routers, state libraries, or CSS systems.
- Do not replace Tailwind with custom CSS; keep responsiveness via Tailwind classes.

## Guardrails
- Preserve responsive class intent (`max-*`, `sm/md/lg/xl`, `wide`) and grid/flex breakpoints.
- Prefer minimal diffs: change text/assets/tokens first; only touch component structure if required for branding.
